==In popular culture==
"Some Nights" appeared in the series finale of ''[[Harry's Law]]'', and has been used in television spots for the [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] program ''[[Secret Millionaire]]''. The song was also used in promos for the [[2012 MTV Movie Awards]] and the [[2013 BCS National Championship Game]]. Fun performed the song on ''[[The Colbert Report]]'', ''[[Late Night with Jimmy Fallon]]'', ''[[Sunrise (Australian TV program)|Sunrise]]'', ''[[The Jonathan Ross Show]]'', and ''[[Saturday Night Live]]''.<ref>{{cite news |url= http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/11/04/fun-snl-some-nights-carry-on_n_2072882.html |title= Fun. On 'SNL': 'Some Nights' And 'Carry On' (VIDEO)|work= [[The Huffington Post]] |accessdate= November 25, 2012 |first=Madeline |last=Boardman |date=November 4, 2012}}</ref> It also was used in trailers and advertisements promoting the Disney animated film ''[[Wreck-It Ralph]]''.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://1061evansville.com/wreck-it-ralph-trailer-features-fun-song-video/ | title = Wreck-It Ralph Trailer Features FUN. Song [VIDEO]
 | first = Kat | last = Mykals | date = October 12, 2012 | accessdate = January 13, 2019 | publisher = [[WDKS]]}}</ref>

The [[Chicago Blackhawks]] use the song as a backing track in several promotional montages.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://video.blackhawks.nhl.com/videocenter/console?id=260964|title=We Stand for You: Cup edition Video – NHL VideoCenter – Chicago Blackhawks|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://video.blackhawks.nhl.com/videocenter/console?id=194997|title=The Hawks Stand For You Video – NHL VideoCenter – Chicago Blackhawks|publisher=}}</ref>

[[Southwest Airlines]] used the song in the first TV spot for their "Welcome Aboard" ad campaign, which was also their first campaign by [[TBWA/Chiat/Day]].

[[Ryan Seacrest|''On Air With Ryan Seacrest'']] reviews a collaborative video version of ''Some Nights'' performed by nine, "[[YouTube]] stars". Produced by Jake Coco and [[W. G. Snuffy Walden]], vocalists include Jake Coco, Corey Gray, Caitlin Hart, Madilyn Bailey, [[Savannah Outen]], [[Jess Moskaluke]], [[Sara Niemietz]], Eppic, and Black Prez.<ref>{{cite web|last=Vulpo|first=Michael|title=YouTube Stars Collaborate for Cover of Fun's 'Some Night'' [VIDEO]|url=http://ryanseacrest.com/2012/08/13/jake-coco-other-youtube-stars-collaborate-for-cover-of-fun-s-some-nights-video/|work=Some Nights|publisher=Ryan Seacrest Productions|accessdate=16 August 2012|location=Los Angeles, California|date=13 August 2012|quote=On Air with Ryan Seacrest}}</ref> Released on Jake Coco's YouTube channel on August 11, 2012, by October 13, 2012 this cover version received 4,532,233 views in 64 days.<ref>{{cite web|last=Coco|first=Jake|title=Some Nights – Fun – Official YouTuber Music Video – Jake Coco & Friends|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kQsN-pvokrw|work=Some Nights|publisher=Jake Coco: Official YouTube Channel|accessdate=13 October 2012|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6BO4wiGYS|archivedate=13 October 2012|format=Video}}</ref> In August 2012 Some Nights was covered by Canadian band Walk Off The Earth for their YouTube channel. Ohio based metalcore band [[Like Moths To Flames]] covered the song on the compilation album ''[[Punk Goes Pop 5]]''.

[[Ellie Goulding]] has covered the song as well in late 2012 on [[BBC Radio]] in the "Live Lounge".

The song was covered by the New Directions glee club in the "[[Dynamic Duets]]" episode of ''[[Glee (TV series)|Glee]]''.

On April 25, 2013, teen actress and musician [[Victoria Justice]] (of [[Nickelodeon]]'s ''[[Victorious]]'') posted a softer acoustic rendition of "Some Nights".<ref>{{YouTube|hFo4PtNMYoc|Victoria Justice – "Some Nights" (fun. cover)}} (uploaded April 25, 2013)</ref><ref>[http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/04/26/victoria-justice-covers-f_n_3163043.html Victoria Justice Covers fun.'s 'Some Nights' (VIDEO)] – ''[[The Huffington Post]]'' (released April 26, 2013)</ref>

[[A cappella]] group [[Straight No Chaser (group)|Straight No Chaser]] released a mashup of this song and "[[We Are Young]]" for their 2013 album ''[[Under the Influence (Straight No Chaser album)|Under the Influence]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Collar|first=Matt|url=http://allmusic.com/album/under-the-influence-mw0002507645|title=Under the Influence – Straight No Chaser|website=Allmusic|accessdate=2 November 2014}}</ref>

The song was covered [[The Band Perry]] in concert from Jackson MI ''We Are Pioneers World Tour'' 2013 with mashup "Night Gone Wasted"<ref>{{YouTube|-iEOHCDx8Zw}}</ref>

